Anti-apartheid activist, Walter Sisulu, would've turned 107 today. ANC secretary general, Ace Magashule, will deliver a commemoration address in Bloemfontein. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. BLOEMFONTEIN - ANC secretary general, Ace Magashule, will deliver the Walter Sisulu commemoration lecture on Saturday in Bloemfontein. The anti-apartheid activist would have turned 107 years on the day. READ: All eyes on Ramaphosa’s next Cabinet Joining Magashule on the list of speakers at the Waaihoek Methodist is ANC NEC member and Sisulu’s daughter, Lindiwe Sisulu and ANC Free State Chairperson Cde Sam Mashinini.